Help.

542
01:12:02,368 --> 01:12:03,849
Please help us.

543
01:12:08,885 --> 01:12:09,995
Easy.

544
01:12:11,170 --> 01:12:13,184
Help us. Wait!

545
01:12:14,674 --> 01:12:17,036
Brother. Please, friend.

546
01:12:18,209 --> 01:12:19,306
Hey, wait!

547
01:12:21,299 --> 01:12:22,501
Don't be afraid.

548
01:12:27,370 --> 01:12:30,891
Wait, brother!
We need to find a village!

549
01:12:35,955 --> 01:12:37,082
What about Luis?

550
01:16:25,455 --> 01:16:27,846
Someone has to show up who can help us.

551
01:16:37,538 --> 01:16:38,997
Nothing but dust here.

552
01:19:03,163 --> 01:19:04,518
It'll do us some good.

553
01:19:59,205 --> 01:20:00,372
It's a good plant.

554
01:20:01,247 --> 01:20:02,288
It'll help us.

555
01:25:23,757 --> 01:25:25,943
Go on, turn it up till it explodes!

556
01:25:33,979 --> 01:25:35,143
Up till it explodes!

557
01:25:53,413 --> 01:25:54,663
Jade!

558
01:25:55,830 --> 01:25:57,143
No!

559
01:26:05,578 --> 01:26:06,628
Jade!

560
01:26:07,913 --> 01:26:09,753
- No!
- Jade!

561
01:26:09,840 --> 01:26:10,993
- Hey!
- Tonin!

562
01:26:11,080 --> 01:26:12,201
- No!
- Tonin!

563
01:26:12,288 --> 01:26:13,868
- Jade!
- Tonin, no!

564
01:26:13,955 --> 01:26:15,288
- Jade!
- No!

565
01:26:19,524 --> 01:26:20,961
Fuck!

566
01:26:23,632 --> 01:26:25,659
What the fuck was that?

567
01:26:25,747 --> 01:26:27,598
We are in a minefield!

568
01:26:43,745 --> 01:26:45,784
Jesus, I'm so high.

569
01:26:46,559 --> 01:26:47,913
I can't think straight.

570
01:27:15,830 --> 01:27:17,070
We're here, Bigui.

571
01:27:18,913 --> 01:27:20,434
There, Bigui, there.

572
01:27:48,965 --> 01:27:51,925
I keep seeing Tonin exploding
in my head.

573
01:28:03,559 --> 01:28:06,206
I've always wanted
to go out in a blaze of glory,

574
01:28:07,604 --> 01:28:08,903
but that...

575
01:28:32,475 --> 01:28:33,705
Hey.

576
01:28:34,353 --> 01:28:37,216
Do you know
what my father said before he died?

577
01:28:37,304 --> 01:28:38,432
What?

578
01:28:40,108 --> 01:28:42,260
"Fuck, it's getting serious."

579
01:28:50,663 --> 01:28:52,930
I couldn't say goodbye to my father.

580
01:29:01,288 --> 01:29:02,330
Jade said,

581
01:29:03,215 --> 01:29:05,080
"Make everything explode."

582
01:29:07,455 --> 01:29:08,565
Typical Jade.

583
01:29:20,163 --> 01:29:21,413
"Pull the brake".

584
01:29:26,205 --> 01:29:28,760
"Pull the brake"
are the last words Esteban heard.

585
01:29:49,830 --> 01:29:52,705
Tonin saw Esteban's body
when he looked over the edge.

586
01:30:00,913 --> 01:30:02,802
We didn't know how to tell you.

587
01:30:15,705 --> 01:30:17,291
I don't want him to stay there.

588
01:31:35,330 --> 01:31:37,361
No idea how we didn't explode earlier.

589
01:31:43,163 --> 01:31:45,065
It must be full of mines here.

590
01:31:48,455 --> 01:31:50,237
We have to reach that mountain.

591
01:31:53,830 --> 01:31:55,211
No mines in the rocks.

592
01:32:53,913 --> 01:32:54,976
Shit.

593
01:34:37,049 --> 01:34:41,118
Let's go!

594
01:34:42,580 --> 01:34:43,830
Let's go!

595
01:34:56,872 --> 01:34:59,663
Not that way!

596
01:35:00,382 --> 01:35:04,153
Go the other way! The other way, fuck!

597
01:35:33,038 --> 01:35:34,595
Follow the truck's path.

598
01:37:07,497 --> 01:37:08,549
No.

599
01:37:17,674 --> 01:37:18,747
Steff?

600
01:37:35,247 --> 01:37:36,763
It's all that's left.

601
01:37:42,038 --> 01:37:43,209
Doesn't matter now.

602
01:37:50,872 --> 01:37:52,663
How many meters to the rock?

603
01:37:58,205 --> 01:37:59,455
Sixty?

604
01:38:02,580 --> 01:38:03,660
Eighty.

605
01:38:10,545 --> 01:38:11,795
Luis!

606
01:38:11,882 --> 01:38:12,924
Hey!

607
01:38:13,580 --> 01:38:14,656
Luis!

608
01:38:18,080 --> 01:38:19,190
What are you doing?

609
01:38:20,684 --> 01:38:21,732
Luis!

610
01:38:22,330 --> 01:38:23,393
Luis!

611
01:39:32,247 --> 01:39:34,086
- I'm coming, Luis.
- Bigui!

612
01:39:34,174 --> 01:39:35,826
You can do it, Bigui.

613
01:39:35,913 --> 01:39:37,038
Luis!

614
01:39:38,372 --> 01:39:39,534
Bigui!

615
01:39:39,622 --> 01:39:40,691
Luis!

616
01:39:46,715 --> 01:39:48,782
Nearly there, Luis!

617
01:39:54,288 --> 01:39:55,532
Bigui!

618
01:39:56,424 --> 01:39:57,919
No. No!

619
01:39:58,663 --> 01:40:00,663
No!

620
01:40:02,190 --> 01:40:03,357
No!

621
01:40:06,233 --> 01:40:07,281
No.

622
01:40:11,580 --> 01:40:12,705
No!

623
01:40:13,663 --> 01:40:14,785
No!

624
01:40:15,421 --> 01:40:16,587
Bigui!

625
01:40:19,538 --> 01:40:20,610
No.

626
01:40:22,372 --> 01:40:23,497
No.

627
01:40:34,413 --> 01:40:36,068
How did you get across?

628
01:40:41,580 --> 01:40:43,288
Bigui followed your steps.

629
01:40:44,632 --> 01:40:45,882
But he exploded.

630
01:40:49,913 --> 01:40:51,830
How? How does this work?

631
01:40:57,913 --> 01:40:58,982
I don't know.

632
01:41:03,122 --> 01:41:04,899
I crossed without thinking.

633
01:41:39,663 --> 01:41:40,705
Like this...

634
01:41:45,663 --> 01:41:48,414
Come on, Josh.
We're going with closed eyes.
